.TH "mutex_lock_interruptible" 9 "mutex_lock_interruptible" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mutex_lock_interruptible \- Acquire the mutex, interruptible by signals.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mutex_lock_interruptible
.BI "(struct mutex *lock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lock" 12
The mutex to be acquired.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Lock the mutex like \fBmutex_lock\fP.  If a signal is delivered while the
process is sleeping, this function will return without acquiring the
mutex.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Process context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if the lock was successfully acquired or -EINTR if a
signal arrived.
